Text
I have to say, this is one of the best Ideas I have seen in a while. RP or PK for
the sheer enjoyment or RPing or PKing, not for any rewards that you might get
from it. How about making it possible to level to 91 by a few different means,
much like the way clans used to be bought and paid for. RP points could still
be awarded, and used as some or all of the cost of making hero, but AQ points,
tokens, or even (Large amounts of) gold could also be required, each being one
part of a way to pay for the advance?

In that light, I might actually suggest keeping the AQ bonuses for PKers the way
they are, because PKers are, indeed, putting everything on the line when they PK.
Giving them the AQ bonus would allow them to meet at least that much of the cost
more easily, and the die-hard RPers get RP points a little easier. Anyone who's
not PK and doesn't RP, will have a little harder time collecting money, AQ 
points, or however they choose to make their mark on the world and become
a hero.

DJ
~
