Sender  Kevin~
Date    Wed Sep 18 22:05:04 2002~
Stamp   1032404704
To      all~
Subject Saving throws news~
Text
I have a new system in place on the test port, and will be testing it over the next week.
This system composes three kinds of saving throws: Fortitude, Reflex, and Will.
All of the existing spells call an opposed check on one of these three saves. Possibly later on,
some physical attacks may also use these values.

"What do those names stand for?"
Fortitude: How well you stand up to body-altering attacks. Poison, disease, etc.
Reflex: Your ability to dodge fireballs, lightning bolts, and otherwise escape harm through agility.
Will: Measure of your willpower; protects against mind-altering magic, divine power, and misc. magic.

"How do I know which spell calls for what save?"
Trial and error, or educated guessing.

I'll get more thorough with this later, as I have to work in the morning.
~
