Stamp   1032490807
To      all~
Subject Spirited Away~
Text
To those of you in the U.S. and Canada,

One of Japan's finest animated movies of all time finally hits our shores.
Sen to Chihiro no Kamikaku shi, or Spirited Away as it's been named in
English, comes out in limited release this Friday, Sept. 20th.

It's a Studio Ghibli film, so if you've seen My Neighbor Totoro, Kiki's
Delivery Serivce, or Princess Mononoke you've got at least a little bit of
an idea of what to expect.  For those that don't, it's better than any
Disney animated movie out there, with more creatures, colors, and plot than
almost any movie brought out today.  It's truly a work of art, not to 
mention a fantastic film.

So if it's in your area of the country, do yourself a big favor and see
Spirited Away on the big screen.  From personal experience, seeing it that
way is a totally different and wonderful feeling than on TV or on a computer.
If it's not in your area this week, it may come next week, with a broader
release.  And if you've got younger siblings, take them along.  It's not for
those under 7, but anyone else will be able to handle the scary parts.

Do yourself a favor as an anime fan, or even just a movie fan and see
this film.


Batanen Fujioka
P.S. And yes, I've heard the dub is actually pretty good.  Don't let that
scare you off!
~
