On friday I believe, I was autoquesting in dante's, and when requesting a summon, I got jumped by
Megua, who set pk to kill me.  Of course he looted 2 herons off my courpse and a seeder with the tokens/
qjunk in it.  Everything he did is legal from what I understand but here's what's suspicious.  Xrkyl
Killed him the very next day, and what do you know... 4 herons were gone (the 2 he had plus the 2 he; note + Got from me) as well as the -seeder-.  As Fascreth and Xrkyl agree, I'm very confident that megua transed
them to a different character.  Now, I understand people probably break the rules all the time, and not
everybody gets caught, but this is a different case.  He was not pkset... then he set PK to kill me, and
now all his AQEQ is probably on a non pkset char again.

I dont mean to sound like a whinny pker, and I know if I didnt want to risk losing them I shouldnt have been
Pkset in the first place, but this is wrong.  It may be piddly bullsh*t to you all, but I worked hard
just to watch those go away to a cheater.  If he would have kept them on his character I would have
no complaints.  To me it is a big deal, I understand I will probably not ever see those herons again
but you all should know.  Thanks for your time.


-Zekim
PS the herons were lvl 48 and 52 I believe.  (48 for sure, 50-something on the other)
~
