Sender  Fatetaf~
Date    Thu Sep 26 14:15:56 2002~
Stamp   1033067756
To      all~
Subject Note, not news. : This I would change.~
Text
Well, since my super sexy news actually got the attention I was looking for. (cheap shot) Here's the things I would do, if given the chance.
Note : Not all the things I would do, but a start on what I would do, if I had the power to do it.

1.)Bring back shimmering floating stones.
I had already explained why, in my news.

2.)Adjust a large majority of stock weapons.
I have a big list of things from players. Speaking of which, I still need to reward people from that "quest." heh.
But the reason I would change weapons, is because right now, a majority of them suck in lower ranges.
There are no axes, no spears, no polearms and things like that.
That would be easy to change.

3.)I would meddle with stock now. 
Blue guard equipment could be made better, more sets of armor could be thrown in on already existing mobs, you know simple things like that.
Blades of poison could be made what they used to be.
More weapons could be brought up to blade of poison stature.
Imagine an axe that would be great for a newbie?! My gosh!

Now, here's where I think the expansion on "making the game better" took the wrong turn.
We wanted balance.
People settled upon that's, and that's spifforific.
However, it wasn't incredibly smart the way it was done.
Maybe what, like four people got together and decided the way to take?
Well, my method is just one person, ME making the decision to set it back and fix it.

However, unlike those before, I thought this out awhile and learned from thier mistake.
They created an even bigger gap of insanely powerful people and insanely weak people.
Characterwise, I mean.

The average person doesn't have super high damage roll equipment. 
The above average person does. 
Now, it used to be average people could get super high dam-roll equipment

See, but here's the thing.
Here's where we went ash-tray.
We could have just edited skills, spells and dam/hit rolls to a somewhat "compromise" face. 
We didn't do that.
Instead, we ripped out things that seemed too fun then went along and bitchz0red skills.

See, I came to realize something.
We'll never get balance here. However.
I've got a new aim.
Fairness.

With balance, you've got the really bad and the really good trying to outweigh each other.
I'll explain it pkwise.
We want each race/class to have more or less the same chance to kill each other.
That's without equipment or fancy tactics.
Then things will be fair.

It's slightly different than balance. I'm not a philosopher so, whatever.

This is what I want to happen.
That's my idea of a first step.
Is that what we wanna take?
~
Sender  Tima~
Date    Thu Sep 26 14:32:28 2002~
Stamp   1033068748
To      all~
Subject Viral quest info~
Text
By now, some of you have recieved various base chemicals. They are for 
use in the Viral quest that will be running very soon.

This will be a team event. Meaning that while everyone will be awarded, 
the team that gains the overall victory will gain a special prize for 
each member. Each team will consist of a minimal of five members of 
preferrably different class and levels. I don't want to see five level 
90 demon warriors running about as a team or something of the like. Be 
diverse. Note your team application to me with the following:

Team name:
Team Captain:
Members and their Race/Class/Level:
Where you'll station your hq: (so I can easily get to your group when need be)
And finally, if you or your members can rp:

---------
The rules:

This is how things will be played out. This will be an rp/pk type 
quest, so you'll want to at least consider paying attention to various 
rp events that may happen in the quest and act accordingly.

The quest works like this: During any of my events, all players are 
infected by a virus that will randomly kill one of you at varied 
intervals. You'll need to work as a team to accomplish the goals since 
you can easily lose a key teammate. In order to stop this virus, your 
job is to construct an antivirus to counter it. A temporary one is 
known, but it'll only help you but so much. (hint hint: look at the rpnote for it)

After tonight's quest, base chemicals will no longer be given as 
prizes. They will have to be bought or found on the mud. You may 
consider this unfair, but I assure you that it'll be worth it in the 
end.

Now, pay attention. These are your base chemicals:
Nysidium Blue
Insidium Red
Xynaid 32
Acidic Kuwanger Extract
Nano-Assembler

From these, you'll need to find a way to create the antivirus. Shortly 
after this note, I'll be hiding eight torn pages of the printout on the 
antivirus across the mud. Yes, they're nolocate. Once you find one, 
simply type 'look research' to find if it holds any info that may be of 
use. These pages will give you an idea of how to create the antivirus. 
Now.. if you decide to share this info with rival teams.. that's your buisness.

In order to mix the chemicals each time, you'll need a seeder. These 
also will no longer be handed out and will need to be bought or found 

Current price conversions for items may depend on if they're auctioned 
or bought from Halperia or Lilith. In order to buy from either, some 
form of rp is needed. Please do try to rp nicely.. they might get upset if you act
like a fool and leave.

Starting prices will be as follows (If bought from halperia or lilith):
Nysidium Blue: 10000 gold per item or 3 per token
Insidium Red: 10000 gold per item or 3 per token
Xynaid 32: 10000 gold per item or 3 per token
Acidic Kuwanger extract: 10000 gold per item or 3 per token
Nano-Assemblers: One token per assembler.
Seeder unit: One token per unit
Seeder pack with one of each base chemical: 3 tokens

Yes, the prices are rather steep. So it's best to know how to mix what 
or go out to find items instead. As previously stated.. this quest will 
have a good payoff in terms of awards. So spend a little, get something 
better in return. Besides, it'll give you gold and token hoarders something to
do while getting more stuff to hoard ^_-

Stay tuned for notes on Tools and quest prizes later today.
~
