Sender  Batanen~
Date    Thu Sep 26 15:18:53 2002~
Stamp   1033071533
To      all~
Subject Changes and such~
Text
I've already talked to Fatetaf, and there's stuff I agree with him on,
and there's stuff I don't.  To those of you who keep saying he's 100% right,
listen up.  Because there needs to be some thinking involved here.

Alright.  First off, we'll talk about stock equipment.  There's a big agreement
that nerfing the equipment before wasn't a great idea.  That is true.  However,
since we can't simply go back to previous areas, since we don't have them,
stop trying to come up with that idea.  In fact, drop all the quick fix ideas
right now.  Remember Fatetaf said things weren't thought out before?  Quick fixes
aren't either.  Now that's been said, we do need to make stock equipment better.
Since Murasame hasn't been logging in very much, I've asked Fatetaf to build
an area with the idea of what equipment should be like, a new area.  This is a
dual function, one is that we can see what his idea is, and whether it's
the right one and to continue from there, and so we can get a new area for
everyone to play.  If his equipment stats are good, peeps on staff can go
through and follow by example, and get stock done right.

The second point, and also an important one is, that people do leave because
they are bored.  So, we need to add more content.  People are much more likely
to either come back or keep playing if new stuff is added.  I've sent a
preliminary proposal for a new class to the IMM staff, and on Saturday, should
have a much better description on skills and spell groups to either code or modify.
This should be a starting point, with possible races as well.  There's been
talk about a better way to handle RP, and much better awards that hopefully will
get finalized soon.  New content will get us more players.  That should
be the vision.  Otherwise, no matter what we change, it's still what we had before, only
with a new coat of wax on it.

So, it's going to take work to get this place better.  That's fact.
Are you willing to help make this place better as a player?


Batanen Fujioka
~
