Sender  Fatetaf~
Date    Fri Sep 27 11:49:05 2002~
Stamp   1033145345
To      all~
Subject Why I quit the immstaff.~
Text
Alright, so incase many of you haven't noticed, I deleted my immortal.
I wasn't fried and I wasn't really "forced" off the staff.

Since I keep getting tells and all that jazz, here's my reasons.

The current immortal staff is not doing what the players want.
When Suzuran brought the mud back up, he made it very clear that the mud was for the players now.
However, that's not the direction the mud is going now.

Players are considered ignorant little children, that can't decide for themselves, apparently.
The current plan of the mud is to rip out and replace things.
Ian/Nothing spent time to think up and draw out plans that are very organized and well thought out.

I uploaded the plans here. : http://www.angelfire.com/ny/xpected/Mud_ideas_Version3.zip

Now, all those plans were ment to replace what we currently have.
Most of the ideas are very good. Very well written and very well thoughtout.
However, with a different face, this is the same thing as 5k.
This is why I've fought so hard to keep what we have.
Also why I wanted us to balance things we currently have.
I was against a rewrite of the mud. I was against the alienation of a player base, just because someone thought it was a good idea and only two other people agreed.

Now, I wrote two news notes. They were both removed.
They were the direction that a majority of the players wanted.
I was overwhelmingly supported by the players.
But, sadly I was lectured and smoked out by the immortals.
Specifically, Batanen and Kevin.

The immortals were suppose to be a team.
Each with different jobs and the like.
Here's where I'm going to admit I'm wrong about something.
I thought the immortals were as a team. And I was under the assumption that this team, would follow what they players wanted.

I was wrong.
The "Team" didn't really exist. I thought it did, but I was wrong.
See, and here's where I was wrong and other ex-immortals were correct.
`4B`$r`&ys`$o`4n`7 was correct. `8S`7e`&i`8T`&z`7e`8r`7 was correct. `1S`!i`&dio`!u`1s`7 was correct. `8M`7ur`&s`7am`8e`7 was correct.
I found myself the only remaining immortal on that staff, that was willing to speak up for the players, when they weren't.

And so, I was told to "Get with the team, or get out."
I will take no part driving the mud in a direction that the players don't want. 
I deleted. That's why. Plain and simple.

Bryson saw it, I owe him an apology for taking the actions I did against him.
Seitzer saw it, he was momentarily part of "The team". He was told to go code something in notepad and to be quiet.
Sidious saw it, he made a lot of noise, got frustated and he deleted.
Murasame saw it, I owe him an apology as well.
I owe murasame a policy because I made thought I was a part of "The team" and I wasn't.
While I was trying to get in what the players want, it was not working with a team that he wanted.

Lastly. Everything is always a "Comprimise"
It's a comprimise between what they players really want and what Batanen and Kevin want.
I won't comprimise. I wanted things changed to the way they were, as well as the other players.

I ask the players, not to compromise either.
You were promised the mud was now for you.
But the way things are turning, it's not.
It's for whoever gets lucky enough to get immed because they're someone's buddy.

So, I'm not going to stand up and scream while you, the players are whispering in my ear what to do.
Say things yourself. You put an unfair burden on me.
With that, I post this note. Foom.

