Sender  Batanen~
Date    Fri Sep 27 15:16:56 2002~
Stamp   1033157816
To      all~
Subject Checks, Balances, and no one person is right~
Text
We'd like to thank Fatetaf for his rant.  Thank you.

As Fatetaf said, he wasn't willing to compromise.  He wanted to have the
final word on everything.  He was going to be the savior of Anime, bringing
fun once again to this supposedly woeful place.  I think I've heard this
one before.  Yup, I believe we heard this when Kyrn came back and made his
big set of sweeping changes.  Did no one question him then?  Sure, but
he was the boss, the had the final say, no one could argue with him.
That's a recipe for disaster.

No matter what the system is, there must be checks and balances.  That's what
I wanted.  The question "Are we doing what's right?" is fair game at all times.
I asked of Fatetaf to show me that what he'd be doing was right on equipment,
before actually working on it.  Seeing that he's only done claneq, I felt this
was a fair thing to ask.  He doesn't, because he did not want his authority
challenged.  Without challenge, one becomes a tyrant, must that he is
portraying I am.

The "players" voice is not one, but many.  Compromise within these voices
is necessary.  And I expect the changes that I'd like to put in here to be
questioned, to be asked, "Are we doing what's right?"  I've posted ideas before
I've either implemented them, or ditched because it was stupid.  This isn't
anything new, folks.  The changes we have planned will be scrutinzed as
well.  Expect for me to get some volunteers on Saturday to come look
at what Kevin's been up to, this has been planned for a while now.

So I expect opinions, reasoning, and compromise to decide where we go
from here.  That's what I meant from asking people if they are willing
to help.  This shouldn't be done alone, and can't be done alone.


Batanen Fujioka
~
