In the Words of James Madison in The Federalist Papers...
"To put the power of an entire people in the hands of one group or person... that is the very definition of Tyranny"
Madison also suggested that, to make government work, you needed separation of powers.
Fatetaf was saying that he needed the final say.
But to say he was being a tyrant is not true, because Fatetaf had the support of the people
We need to separate the powers of the Imms. They need to have less say in the direction of the mud
While the mortals need more say.
Anyone interested in more theories by Madison (which i believe could benefit the mud.)
Can read Federalist 47, 48, and 51.

