Sender  Sirus~
Date    Fri Sep 27 16:10:37 2002~
Stamp   1033161037
To      all~
Subject The Change Looms overhead.~
Text
Concern is a good thing. Scratch that, it's a great thing.

This whole ordeal is starting to erupt into a piss-party of drama,
which if the last time I checked, was something none of us liked.
AnimeMUD, granted, used to be a blast. I left Immship elsewhere over
five years ago to start playing here as a mortal. It was fun. The
main meat and bone of the game was it's outrageousness. However, it's
`&time has past``. Can we bring it back? Sure. Should we? Certainly.

However... '`&Should we make it like it was before?``' In my wise and
player-driven opinion, `&no.``' You see, AnimeMUD's charm was old-school.
Times have changed. MUD's all over have gotten bigger, badder and far
cooler then the days of yore. `&We need to take it up a notch.``'

Take this as an example. Video games. Personally, I loved all those
classis Nintendo and Super Nintendo games to death. They were the best
games ever. However, with the new, more powerful systems available,
who would want to play a NES graphic/diffucultly/control style game
on a PS2 or Xbox or whatever? I wouldn't. I would want to play a game
which uses those elements to make it great.

What I'm saying is this. Let's not sit here and be pissy because
things aren't '`&the way they used to be``'. Because dwelling on the past
will only make us miss the fact that we can use the old-school goodness
to make a new-school masterpeice. Fun as hell to play. Remember those
days way back when that you could kill hour after hour here? I do.
And it '`&can and will happen again.``' Have a little faith in us.

Keep in mind, my opinions about this have not fully been voiced. Not
to the players, not the Immstaff, not really anyone. Until now.
And from here on out, it's time that things do change. So, come along
for the ride. If we try to make something new and cool and fail, isn't
that '`&better then never trying at all?``'

"Don't you want to be an AnimeMUD superstar?"

Sirus.
~
Sender  Daltigoth~
Date    Fri Sep 27 17:36:15 2002~
Stamp   1033166175
To      all~
Subject Stuff.~
Text
Well, damn.

The other day, when I saw that note from batanen, saying
that he was going to have Don start building an area, I really
had my hopes up. That seemed to me to be a huge, positive
step in the right direction. Unfortunatly that has blown up, apparently.
It looks to be largely due to a clash of egos, whatever people say.
Thats the way it always is here, it seems.

Anyway, how about someone actually continue that line of thought?
Someone on the imm staff, or someone should be brought on to, build
an area with eq better than whats out there now, for a wide range of levels,
then they should bring a couple flunkies on to go through the rest
of the areas on the mud to bring the place up to that area's level.

Juice up aqeq some as well. give chocos an additional +2 to all stats,
that would put them up to being fairly worthy pieces of eq.
Beef dim shields, etc etc.

Shims. Ah, shimmies. Yeah they were neat, but perhaps
they were a little over the top. Perhaps put in a weaker-ish version of them?
+3 to all stats, and +2 hit/dam or something?

You know what else should be done, to give lowbies an easier/funner time of
it? Take all of the stat boosts granted by the sub issue eq, and double them.
plain and simple.

-shrug- So it makes the game easier? Oh well. If people have to work
for everything, it becomes just that, work. Not play, which it should be.

Bring back oldschool? You know what I say? I say f-ck that. Oldschool
was lame for anyone who wasn't in one of the power cliques.

As far as quests go? Start handing out more stuff! Tokens DON'T need
to be only handed out a single one to the winner of a quest which took hours.
Give the poor people a chance to get them too, reward entire quests with 1 per 
person for quests where everyone tried hard, just give the winners something more

Oldschool AnimeMud is dead. Yeah. Rest in Peace, we will have
fond memories of it forever probably. However this doesn't mean that
what the place is now can't kick ass with a little work, too.

Ah, this has been the 2nd long note I have posted in as many days, sorry.

`8d`#.`!.`1.`8Here in 1 form or another since late 1997. And will probably still be here in 2010, if the place is still alive`#.`!.`1.`7
