Text
Don't pull that fuckhead dartout bullshit when I'm trying to clear up missunderstandings.  It's irritating beyond belief.
As hard as this is for me, i'm going to continue and attempt to clear this up.  Forgive me if I get a little pissed off at the way you treated me.

I'll continue where I left off.

I offered you the seeder/etc in exchange for the BP because I thought it would be a fair exchange/mutually benefitial.  Let me explain.

The BP is for personal prizes.  The team stuff/etc will have it's own unique prizes handed out for the entire team.

BP:  Single person prizes.  Seeder/etc stuff:  Team prizes

Seeing as you totally have this quest wrapped around your finger, what with your unlimited resources and drafting of every single person that got a printout, noone else has a reasonable chance at this quest.

Unfortunately, this I did not discover until AFTER I had invested much time, effort, and the very last of my resources, into participating.

Anyways, as to not go too far into THAT, as it is not immediately related to this, I will get right down to the point.

I did not offer you the seeder/etc for the BP in any attempt to screw you over.  Nor did I do so because I thought the BP would have a higher value than the seeder/etc.  I did so because I have no chance at the seeder stuff.  Thanks to you.

I figured in order to win anything, I have to settle for the smaller/less extravigant solo prizes.  I wanted to trade you trade-in stuff for the team prize, for trade in stuff for the lower prize.

Of course, you had to go off on some tangent as soon as the offer was made, assuming that there must be something extremely valuable about the BP, immediately refusing my offer and then trying to buy my stuff anyways with worthless crap I have no 
use for.

I did not try and "rip off" your bp for some less-valuable stuff.  I was trying to find a way for me to get out of the team quest, while still getting some sort of small prize.  But no.  You had to go off on your greed trip, assuming I was after y
your loot, bs, whatever.  Truth is, I wanted it to work out so we could both have a better chance at winning something.  But you just insist on being the sole winner of everything.  Very sad.  After everything you've done, I should have expected t
this.  It's the one thing on which I'll admit my ignorance.

I apologize for the fomat.  However, that is all I apologize for.  You're the one that's in the wrong here.  You have no idea how cruel it is to take someones offer, and then change your mind about selling right after the fact.

You and that greed of yours.  It's not enough that something's mutually benefitial.  Noo, you have to make sure you come out on the top two-fold.  That's fine.  I can't understand the ethics behind it, but whatever.

I'd appreciate it if you'd keep our discussion between us, but hey. I understand if you don't.  I mean, it wouldn't surprise me if you had everyone turned against me.  I've come to expect such.

Anyways, either way, I'd appreciate atleast a responst saying that you took the time to read.  Don't worry, i'm not expecting one.  But it would be mildly kind to atleast acknowledge you didn't just skip this like I figure you did.

It's a shame I have to write this instead of confronting you about it, but you're the one that ran out.  Anyways, I'm done.
