Sender  Kevin~
Date    Sun Sep 29 16:04:50 2002~
Stamp   1033333490
To      all~
Subject Balance, PK, powergaming, etc.~
Text
Let me start off by addressing a few problems in the MUD.
Some of these you might agree with, others not; I'll tell you how I think it is in all honesty.

`!W`1ARNING``: Read no further if you think you'll be offended; chances are you will.


With that disclaimer out of the way, here I go.

`^1`6)`` Powergaming.
One of the things which I believe made us stand out from other muds, early on,
was our flashy multi-hit spells and skills. While they do look nice, they also
have engendered a dangerous mentality in the player base. To quote Valorath,
"that mud is based off of too much damage, too quickly. It's funny when people
complain because they can't kill everything in 1 round."

`^2`6)`` PK / NonPK.
Most of the players were PK in the early days of this MUD, and thus the creed
of the day would have been balance between the classes. Today, the majority of
the pbase is NonPK. This hinders my ability to balance out skills and spells,
when I run the risk of stepping on the toes of those whom the balance issue
does not concern at all. Pleasing both the PKers and NonPKers has become
a Herculean task, when the mud is becoming more and more NonPK.

`^3`6)`` Equipment.
Most of you know how varied equipment stats are. Some stock items are highly
sought after, and autoquest equipment is nearly out of control. Also, pieces
of old quest equipment still linger about here on the MUD. Some of it is
questionable, while others are downright insane. (15/15 av 65 heron)
When this type of gear is considered, EQ can make or break a successful kill.

`^4`6)`` Lock skills.
These fall somewhere inbetween being a problem of their own and contributing
towards problem 1. Their nature is to delay the opponent's command input,
thus hindering spellcasters and melee classes alike. "What's the problem with
them?" They're tactical skills that have been used as a crutch. Spamming trip,
bash, footsweep, etc. does not constitute a strategy.

Here are some possible solutions that I have for these issues.

1) PK / NonPK
Unless someone can come up with a mind-boggling way of keeping both of these
in focus, one or the other will demand priority. PK wants balanced gameplay,
while NonPK wants innovation and expansion.

2) Equipment
The PK autoquesting bonus, from what I heard, was a failure. Now there is
more level 20 AQEQ in circulation. There isn't an easy answer to this, other
than removing the problematic gear.

3) Lock skills
Valorath has suggested that an anti-locking timer accompany the lag skills,
in order to make PK something other than a spamfest.

These aren't etched in stone, so don't start spamming the note board because I
merely suggested something that you disagree with.

Kevin - "`&Right now, I feel like Atlas.``"

P.S. Fatetaf, I think your recent course of action is petty.
P.P.S. Thanks for the help, 9k10 testers.
P.P.P.S. My nose itches.
~
