Subject Re : kevin~
Text
Heh. Wow. I must have really gotten to you.

I wasn't really being petty.
Petty means it doesn't have importance.
I guess you'll have to pull out thesaurus and look for a spiffy adjective to use.

What I did, however was the mark of a true superhero.
I felt it was important. Otherwise, I wouldn't have done it.

I don't need to speak in riddles and sway the people with bells and whistles,
I do everything in a crude manner and I put all my cards on the table.
That's why people didn't like me. You know what I was about, I don't need to 
hide behind anything. 

I wanted the mud one way.
I know I wasn't the only one, so don't give me that crap, about being selfish.

If I was selfish, I would have pushed for changes only I wanted.
Ones that only bettered my alts or my interests.
I didn't do that at all.
Instead of arguing and trying to drive the mud in the way I wanted, I gave up my imm.
There was one other option I could have taking reguarding deleting.
I could have given up what I wanted, ignored alot of players and worked with the other immortals
In getting what they wanted.
I wasn't going to do that. I'm not that selfless.

I gave up my position of "power".
If I was petty, I woulda just went and char_fryed a few players, advanced some others
and cheated my own alts. You don't see me doing that, so don't even imply it.

The game in general, was getting me angry.
I spent a lot of time trying to better the place.
Each time, it got me angrier and angrier.

I had to post like 6 notes just to get possess removed.
And that's something everyone had settled on was broken. Even those that had it.

And how many times did it take me for kevin to getup off his ass, just to 
stop coding guns for a day, to fix races?
Everything was always a fight, a fight then a comprimise.
Screw that. I have enough problems without having to come to a place where 
i'm suppose to have fun, just to argue.
When it comes down to it, I realized it's just a game. It was for fun.
To me, that's all I wanted it to be about fun.
It's not about proving a point, it's not about winning. That doesn't mean I won't.

I deleted my immortal. Very petty huh?
The "team" as you call it, wanted something else.
I didn't. Plain and simple.
Petty, Stepping aside and letting others get what they want.
Do whatever you want.
I'm sure you will.

Now a couple players, without saying your names,
I have lost a lot of trust.
You wanted something, I tried for it, then you withdrew support.
You know who you are. Peh.

And one more thing.

P.S.Kevin, you're a pathetic, largely overweight, gun totting red-neck. I hope you enjoy a job flipping hamburgers.

P.P.S Batanen, you look like the blue ranger. Your girlfriend is fat.
~
