Subject Noble Causes~
Text
Who gives a shish what the IMMs think?
I don't care what Fatetaf wants, what Batanen or Kevin want, or what Sirus/Kurusa/Adapa/etc want..

I also don't care what the mortals want.
Nor do I care what -I- want.

However, I do believe that what the mortals want is what is important.
Without them, this place is a bunch of powerful gods with no followers.
Fatetaf had his ideas, and A lot of the mortals agreed with them.
Batanen has had some ideas that the mortals want as well recently.
Unfortunetely, I think that Fatetaf wanted what the mortals wanted, and that is what was important.
I don't care what anyone wants, I just want to do my job and have quests.
But I do want to see the right thing done, and the mortals get what the want.
This doesn't mean to give them all the eq and crap in the mud.
IMMs shouldn't be here to come up with ideas, they should be here to decide which mortal
ideas to implement, since without anyone to believe in a god, does that god really exist anymore?
The IMMs here derive their power from the mortals, and so the mortals should 
have some say in what goes on with the mud. Which is what it looked like Fatetaf was
trying to accomplish, at least in someway.
Sad to see him go. If only the "group" of us up here could start listening more.
sure, we listen a little bit, but we also get too focused on what we want.
I think we need to focus on what the mortals want, and decide which of it to put in.
(JEez, I keep saying the same things, right? well, it's because it is important.)

And that is what I think.

`8S`7o`&d`7i`8e``
~
