We all get pissed when certain changes, which we find asinine, are thrown in.  Like Juraians.

Also, you say you need to undo the damage Biryu and Vorlin caused.  Who's to say, in 2 years or however
long it takes, somebody won't come along and want to undo the damage YOU caused.  See, "damage" in that
form is strictly subjective.  Subjectivity leads to bias, bias leads to hate, hate leads to suffering, etc.

If you want mortal input on changes, and you want to do things democratically, nothing will ever, ever get done.
People won't vote against changes they don't want because they're lazy or French or something, then
they'll bitch when the changes win the majority and are put in.  That's how democracy works.
Nothing is ever your fault, but damned if you can't complain about it anyway.  That's how we've been working,
or not working, as the case may be.

Personally, I don't care anymore.  I really don't.  Whatever happens here, I'll log on, I'll chat, I'll idle.
Maybe it'll come back, maybe not.  Who knows, who cares.  Life goes on.  The extent to which I'm bitter has
actually surprised me on numerous occassions; I used to adore this place like no other.  Time and time again,
though, dumb shit happens that just irritates me further and further.  It's not about fun anymore, it's about
politics.  I hate politics.

That's all.  Your quest timer is up, shouldn't you be out killing that same mob again?

