Maybe I shouldn't be putting my $.02 in this time, but fsck it.

This thing with Fatetaf and the whole nine yards. Well, I could
simply corner certain parties and say my peice, but maybe this is
something most people need to hear. All of this in-fighting and
drama (and that's what it is, Days of our AnimeMUD), is all over
some difference of opinion.

You see, I'm a firm believer that Don is a wanker, and I'm sure he
thinks the same about me. However, I have talked to Don enough to
know he has damn good ideas and a noble cause for this MUD. It's a
shame some of those venues he piqued up about won't be explored.

Also, on the other side of all of this, Batanen and Kevin have a
vastly different view of AnimeMUD and what it -should- be. Myself,
I have a WAY different view of what needs to be done here in order
to right the wrongs done by Biryu, Vorlin, etc. (And this in no way
is meant to be a flame on Biryu and Vorlin, they too had a noble
cause for AnimeMUD)

The problem is getting together and finding a solution as a team.
