Sender  Kevin~
Date    Fri Oct  4 18:10:39 2002~
Stamp   1033773039
To      all~
Subject Stats: What they do / what I want them to do~
Text
Someone curious about what this whole stats thing I've been working on is about?
Let me illustrate what the stats do now, and what I hope for them to do.

`!S`1trength``
`8==`7=`&==`7=`8==``
Now: Affects ability to push/drag, wield/dual wield weapons, counterattack,
bash, throw, disarm, carry weight, hitroll/damroll(minor).

Later: Affect damroll to a greater extent, and in turn affect the damage of
physical attack skills. Affect shield block rate.

`@I`2ntelligence``
`8==`7==`&====`7==`8==``
Now: Affects learning rate, speed of skill improvement, brew/scribe success
rate, fear spell, mana recovery rate.

Later: Affect spell damage in a way similar to that of Strength w/physical
attacks, and success rate of phase body.

`#W`3isdom``
`8=`7=`&==`7=`8=``
Now: Affects practice gains, brew/scribe success rate, mana gains/recovery.

Later: Affect duration of spells and success rate of parry.

`$D`4exterity``
`8=`7==`&===`7==`8=``
Now: Affects counterattack success rate, bash, dirt kick, trip, dragon punch,
hurricane kick, optic blast, feed, footsweep, roundhouse, disarm, flashkick,
smoke bomb, kamehameha wave, pounce, rapid strike, heat metal spell, move
gains/recovery rate.

Later: Affect hitroll in a manner similar to that of Strength and damroll,
affect success rate of dodge.

`%C`5onstitution``
`8==`7==`&====`7==`8==``
Now: Affects hp gains, hp recovery rate.

Later: Affect success rate of dodge/parry on victim's side, amount of healing
from curative spells


For the existing functions, they would be rewritten to keep faith with the
stats system when it's expanded.
Now, the 'permanent' stats are the only ones which will affect permanent
gains. (HP/Mana/Movement/Practices) Wearing a shimmy or whatnot will NOT
make your HP gains soar like the Soviet/US astronaut campaign from the 1960s.

They will, however, affect `&=== `8every other aspect `&===`` associated with the
stat increases. Moral of the story? Train your stats to keep HP, moves, mana,
and practices high. You can also opt for instant gratification by training
hp/mana/movement(practice converting still in debate), but early investment
will give a more desirable payoff.

Kevin - "`&Got twink?``"

(P.S. Read 'expanded' as 'doubled to at least twice its current range'.)
~
