Hey, look at me, I'm back on after a month or so of not bein around, I think. I
honestly cannot remember the last date I was here, but I remember why I left. I
let Dorath borrow my kaiserflares so they wouldn't be looted off of me, so what
happens? Someone looted them from him. *sigh* Kemoh must have left a curse on
me or something. In any case this whole thing is ridiculous. Honestly I have never
witnessed so much testosterone pissed in multiple directions at once. Loki was
right, this isn't about changes or what who wants, this is DramaMUD. Honestly,
you guys can't stop for a second to consider what consequences your actions will
have. You ever hear the saying every pebble in the pond makes a ripple across the
whole pond? Well right now were looking at quite the $hitstorm. Immortals need
to chill the hell out on each other. There shouldn't even BE politics involved
in a text based game. It should be whatever is more fun, whatever will bring up
the pbase numbers, and whatever is within conceivable limits to create to achieve
those goals. Those should be the ONLY politics around here. You guys obviously
have differences and such, that's fine. However, when these differences begin to
affect the destiny of a f*cking GAME, now let's get descriptive.

Pronunciation: 'gAm Function: noun a (1) : activity engaged in for diversion or 
amusement : PLAY (2) : the equipment for a game b : often derisive or mocking jesting 
: FUN, SPORT

Fun, Play, Sport, Game, the things this is supposed to be without all the physical
activity. Now it sounds to me as though some sort of devious ideas and obscure
plots are being played out behind the scenes of what the Immortals I guess consider
an ignorant mob, being the player base. What will this achieve exactly? Why are
even fighting about anything? No one needs to be right, no one has to be wrong,
no one needs to be a messiah, and no one needs to be some sort of vile super villian.
Popularity contests are won by rich and (defined by soceity) good looking people. 
We all gathered here cause we didn't win those. Here we got imagination, destruction
mudslinging and the whole nine yards life has without the actual feeling of it
except for the burn of other peoples words. So leave it at imagination and 
destruction. Cause hey, I love watching $hit go BOOM! Heh.

