Sender  Shiori~
Date    Sat Oct  5 19:20:01 2002~
Stamp   1033863601
To      immortal~
Subject Quest stuff~
Text
Not really a complaint about the quest system, but something I think needs to be kept in mind.
Basicly, it's this: EVen disregarding any personal issues, Tima needs to be given a break here-
She throws good quests, I dont think anybody disputes that.  The -problem- lies in people(who shall
go unnamed, this isn't the forum for it) harrassing her, and other imms, for quests.  Good quests take
time, planning, and good effort to go off properly- that can't be done more than once a week, usually,
unless it's something like Soccer or Adapa's murderball system.  If imms(in this case, Tima) are continuously
pestered and yelled at for not throwing a quest at the beck and call of certain mortals, it's going to wear them down
eventually.  I think it needs to be made clear that quest imms ARENT there to throw a quest any time
someone wants one- I think they're around to throw high quality, enjoyable quests- even if it takes a while between them.
And if an imm is being harrassed to throw a quest and people wont take no for an answer, that imm needs to be
able to either deal with it themselves, or be able to send something off to an admin and have THEM lay
the smack down- Point is, harrassed quest imms equal unhappy quest imms, and unhappy quest imms
equal a serious lack of quests.  Morale=good, you folks should be allowed to keep yours(and the players, after you're feeling better)
up.
~
